{{ 'dev-tree-fibre-intro.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
{%- comment -%}
  Section: "Tree fibre intro" (dev name `tree-fibre-intro`).
  Figma layer: "Image and text" — desktop 45081:10079 (1440x530), mobile 44850:1731 (375x306).
  Page: Tree-Fibre (NOT the homepage).

  No JS: the Brief's Interactivity section is "none" — a static two-panel content block.
  No slider, accordion, tab, sticky or scroll behaviour, so no dev-tree-fibre-intro.js exists.

  BACKGROUND — read before "fixing" this.
  `--bg` (#FCF5E3, Cream/100) is the CARD's background, not the section's. The section root is
  deliberately TRANSPARENT so the page background (#FFFCF4, Cream/50) shows through the 64px
  side gutters and the 80px top spacer. Sampled straight off the Figma artboard:
    page (10,10)   -> #FFFCF4
    card (300,120) -> #FCF5E3
  Painting --bg on the root would flood those gutters cream and fail the pixel diff outright.

  MOBILE — the image is ABSENT, not reflowed.
  The image block (45081:10088) has no counterpart anywhere in the mobile tree — it is not
  stacked under the text, it simply does not exist there. So it is hidden at <=768px rather
  than being wrapped or re-ordered. (Open question for PM: hard breakpoint rule, as built here,
  or a merchant-facing "show image on mobile" toggle? The design says hard rule; built as designed.)

  DIVIDER — 99x1 rule, inlined from .figma-assets/tree-fibre-intro/divider-desktop.svg.
  The Figma export is a stroked <line>, NOT a <path d>. Its `stroke="#333333"` and geometry
  (y1=0.5 x2=99 y2=0.5, viewBox 0 0 99 1) are reproduced VERBATIM below. Figma's export also
  carried ancestor-context artefacts (a full-canvas page rect, the card rect, a clip-path) which
  are export scaffolding, not the divider's own geometry — asset-prep flagged these explicitly and
  they are correctly omitted.
  The Brief warned the rule "renders visibly lighter" and might carry an unread opacity. It does
  not: sampling the artboard at the divider row (y=283, x=144..242) returns a solid #333333 for
  all 99 px. No opacity is applied and none is invented here.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- comment -%} Fixed design tokens from Figma — not merchant-controlled {%- endcomment -%}
<style>
  .tree-fibre-intro {
    /* Brand params (Brief → Brand Params table). Faces are loaded by snippets/dev-brand-fonts.liquid. */
    --font-body: 'Public Sans', sans-serif;
    --font-heading: 'Test Tiempos Headline', serif;
    --container-max: 1312px;
    --section-px: 64px;
    --section-px-m: 16px;

    /* Typography — desktop */
    --font-heading-size: 32px;
    --font-heading-weight: 400;
    --font-heading-lh: 1.2;
    --font-heading-ls: normal;
    --font-body-size: 20px;
    --font-body-weight: 500;
    --font-body-lh: 1.4;

    /* Typography — mobile: taken from the Mobile artboard, not a scale factor.
       The 0.5px heading letter-spacing is mobile-only and desktop's is unset — a deliberate
       discrepancy read off the layer data (Brief, Note 3). Preserved, not normalised. */
    --font-heading-size-m: 26px;
    --font-heading-ls-m: 0.5px;
    --font-body-size-m: 18px;

    /* Spacing — desktop */
    --spacing-sm: 24px; /* row gap: text card ↔ image */
    --spacing-md: 40px; /* card internal gap: intro → divider → heading */
    --spacing-lg: 80px; /* card padding, all sides */

    /* Spacing — mobile */
    --spacing-md-m: 24px; /* card internal gap */
    --spacing-lg-m: 24px; /* card padding, all sides */

    /* Mobile top spacer is 48px against a desktop 80px. Scaling the merchant's own padding_top
       keeps that relationship intact if they change it. 80 * 0.6 = 48. */
    --pt-scale-m: 0.6;

    /* Layout / decoration */
    --radius: 32px;
    --media-ratio: 644 / 450; /* the image's fixed 450px height is what sets the desktop row height */
    --divider-w: 99px;
    --divider-h: 1px;
  }
</style>

{%- liquid
  # richtext: already-safe HTML from Shopify — never escape it. The <p> wrapper is unwrapped so
  # the copy stays inline inside the <h2> (same idiom as dev-featured-product).
  assign heading_html = section.settings.heading | remove: '<p>' | remove: '</p>'

  assign image = section.settings.image
  assign image_alt = section.settings.alt_text
  if image_alt == blank
    assign image_alt = image.alt
  endif
  assign image_alt = image_alt | default: '' | escape
-%}

<div
  class="tree-fibre-intro"
  style="
    --bg: {{ section.settings.background_color }};
    --color: {{ section.settings.text_color }};
    --accent: {{ section.settings.accent_color }};
    --pt: {{ section.settings.padding_top }}px;
    --pb: {{ section.settings.padding_bottom }}px;
  "
>
  <div class="tree-fibre-intro__inner">
    <div class="tree-fibre-intro__card">
      {%- if section.settings.intro_text != blank -%}
        <div class="tree-fibre-intro__intro">
          {{- section.settings.intro_text -}}
        </div>
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- if section.settings.show_divider -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          Verbatim geometry from .figma-assets/tree-fibre-intro/divider-desktop.svg.
          Do not retype, round, or "tidy" these coordinates.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <svg
          class="tree-fibre-intro__divider"
          width="99"
          height="1"
          viewBox="0 0 99 1"
          fill="none"
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          aria-hidden="true"
          focusable="false"
        >
          <line y1="0.5" x2="99" y2="0.5" stroke="#333333"/>
        </svg>
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- if section.settings.heading != blank -%}
        <h2 class="tree-fibre-intro__heading">{{ heading_html }}</h2>
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>

    {%- if image != blank -%}
      {%- comment -%}
        Desktop/tablet only — hidden at <=768px, where the design has no image at all.
        Source fill is 1058x844, so 1058 is the largest useful width; it renders at 644px
        with object-fit: cover.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="tree-fibre-intro__media">
        {{
          image
          | image_url: width: 1058
          | image_tag:
            loading: 'lazy',
            widths: '400, 600, 800, 1000, 1058',
            sizes: '(min-width: 1440px) 644px, (min-width: 769px) 48vw, 100vw',
            alt: image_alt,
            class: 'tree-fibre-intro__image'
        }}
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>
</div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Tree fibre intro",
  "tag": "section",
  "presets": [{ "name": "Tree fibre intro" }],
  "settings": [
    { "type": "header", "content": "Content" },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "intro_text",
      "label": "Intro text",
      "default": "<p>For decades, tree-fibre has been the go-to material for breathability -from performance sportswear to luxury fashion.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "heading",
      "label": "Heading",
      "info": "Use a line break to split the heading across two lines.",
      "default": "<p>So, we asked -<br/>why not duvets?</p>"
    },
    { "type": "checkbox", "id": "show_divider", "label": "Show divider line", "default": true },
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "image",
      "label": "Image",
      "info": "Shown beside the text on desktop and tablet. The design has no image on mobile, so it is hidden below 768px."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "alt_text",
      "label": "Image alt text",
      "info": "Optional. Falls back to the alt text set on the image in Files."
    },

    { "type": "header", "content": "Colors" },
    {
      "type": "color",
      "id": "background_color",
      "label": "Card background",
      "info": "The cream card behind the text. The section itself stays transparent so the page background shows through.",
      "default": "#FCF5E3"
    },
    { "type": "color", "id": "text_color", "label": "Text color", "default": "#333333" },
    {
      "type": "color",
      "id": "accent_color",
      "label": "Accent color",
      "info": "Focus outlines only — this section has no accent colour in the design.",
      "default": "#333333"
    },

    { "type": "header", "content": "Spacing" },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_top",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 200,
      "step": 4,
      "unit": "px",
      "label": "Padding top",
      "info": "Scales to 60% of this on mobile (80px → 48px), matching the Mobile artboard.",
      "default": 80
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_bottom",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 200,
      "step": 4,
      "unit": "px",
      "label": "Padding bottom",
      "info": "The design has no bottom spacer — the next section's own top spacer carries the gap.",
      "default": 0
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
